cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes methods for training convolutional neural networks with binarized weights and activations, specifically for mobile devices with limited power capacity and computation resources. The focus is on image recognition tasks, which suggests the primary category is likely cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel network decomposition strategy, which involves dividing the network into groups, and proposes extensions for semantic segmentation and object detection tasks. These aspects suggest that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
